	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_SMAN_IEUP_DESTROYER_MISSILE">
			<Text>Missile Destroyer</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_SMAN_IEUP_DESTROYER_MISSILE_STRATEGY">
			<Text>The Missile Destroyer is a fast naval melee attack unit designed to hunt down submarines and to provide anti-aircraft support. It often operates as an escort to embarked units, Battleships and Carriers when in range of enemy planes and subs.  It is quick, having a good chance to withdraw to the rear before an enemy naval melee attack can occur.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_SMAN_IEUP_DESTROYER_MISSILE_HELP">
			<Text>The Missile Destroyer is a fast ship, highly effective at recon, and specialized at hunting down submarines and intercepting aircraft. Fights as a naval melee unit. Can hold 1 Missile. Requires [ICON_RES_OIL] Oil.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_SMAN_IEUP_DESTROYER_MISSILE_PEDIA">
			<Text>
				The Missile Destroyer is an upgrade from the Destroyer unit, and is available on the discovery of Advanced Ballistics. It does not become obsolete. It can carry 1 missile. Requires [ICON_RES_OIL] Oil.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]A Missile Destroyer is a larger, tougher Destroyer capable of carrying missiles. Like the Destroyer, but more so, it is specialized at hunting submarines and intercepting aircraft attempting to attack the larger ships it often escorts.
			</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
	
